
Tracker:

* Bugs: http://sourceforge.net/tracker/?group_id=93707&atid=605270
* RFE: http://sourceforge.net/tracker/?group_id=93707&atid=605273
* Patches: http://sourceforge.net/tracker/?group_id=93707&atid=605272

Old KShutDown 1.0.x features:

* Settings: Local and global shortcuts
* Settings: Notifications
* Settings: Link creator
* Help: Handbook
* Help: "What's this?" context help
* Show warning before action (configurable time)
* Progress bar
* Action configuration (command before action, pause before action)
* Lock screen after login
* Close CD-ROM before logout
* Related KDE settings (kcontrol)
* Trigger: When selected application exit
* Port language translations from KShutdown 1.0.x

Compilation Fixes:

* Make sure all singnal.h, stdlib.h (systemconfig.cpp),
  sys/types.h (appobserver.h) are included

Extras:

* Recent items
* Support for more media players
  (Xine, KMPlayer, MythTV, etc.)

Application observer:

* Fix combo box width
  (http://ariya.blogspot.com/2006/03/resize-pop-up-list-of-combo-box_15.html)

Misc.:

* Optionally (--delay <seconds>) show warning message before action,
  and automatically continue action if no user reaction
* Optionally mute sound (master mixer) before lock screen
* Warn if KDM is not running: https://launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/kshutdown/+bug/42230
* Command line support, execute shell command
* DBUS
* Plasmoid
* KDE Kiosk
* Include in KDE 4
* "K" menu integration
* http://sourceforge.net/forum/forum.php?thread_id=1073402&forum_id=324058
* http://sourceforge.net/forum/forum.php?thread_id=1366875&forum_id=324058
* http://sourceforge.net/forum/forum.php?thread_id=1438962&forum_id=324058
* Automatically chmod /sbin/shutdown, so every user can shutdown or reboot
* Support for GNOME/GDM
* Grayed-out background [by zero]
* Switch to console mode (tty) [by DigitalCyanide]
* Add test button for "Close CD"
* Remember last settings page
* KDM configurator, auto configuration
* Optionally force application exit
* Save KDE session if possible
* Remote reboot or shutdown (via SSH)
* "Shutdown every day on the same time"
* Option to hide main window
* Detect unsaved documents (is there any KDE API to do this?)
* "Switch User" menu functionality
* Command to Reboot Directly into Windows
  (http://sourceforge.net/forum/forum.php?thread_id=1758589&forum_id=324059)

Triggers:

* Activate action when the CPU usage goes under a certain level
  (see http://www.autoshutdown.org/index.html)
  [by aaron-koensgen, luckymancvp]
* Activate action when selected window disapear

Usability:

* http://sourceforge.net/forum/forum.php?thread_id=1639947&forum_id=324058
